 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Farewell!</span><hr size=1> I just wanted to post a follow up and thought I would do it here in the open/greneral forum. I settled my outstanding issues with the arrangements to quit EQ today. I passed guild leadership over to Dpin and handed off pp and equipment that were in the &quot;Guild Bank&quot;. I am making arrangements to cancel my accounts.<br><br>I really enjoyed the time I spent in EQ and the friends I made. I wish you all great luck in Norrath and RL as well. The time has come for Mighty and his crew to fade off into the sunset. I posted my reasons for doing so in a little detail in the guild only forum so I won't go over it here again. But, I would like to add a little before I pass away into the west...<br><br>In the last couple of weeks since stopping EQ, I have:<br><br>1. Really caught up with lost time with my wife and family. It is a blast to have 4 kids and spend time with them and see the joy it creates. Actually talking with my wife without telling her &quot;hold on hun, I am on a CR&quot; is a nice change too.<br><br>2. Worked on the house and my truck after putting it off for way to long.<br><br>3. Played games with my oldest daughter for the first time in a long while without having to hurry because I had to logon to EQ.<br><br>4. Been more productive at work since I am actually working instead of spending time trying to fix the guild web site or write a small book defending my opinions of how a guild should operate.<br><br>5. Saved $50.00 a month in EQ bills <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>6. My arm and wrist don't tingle from bad ergonomics with playing a game on 4 PCs.<br><br>7. Actually been letting my family use the PCs I have for more than 2 minutes at a time.<br><br>8. Gone to bed and gotten up for work on time every day for almost two weeks--a record since I started playing EQ in 1999.<br><br>9. Been able to relax in my down time rather that get worked into a frenzy because of a game.<br><br>I just wanted you all to know that I feel better as a result of making this decision. But, of course, I will miss the game and the friends I made. I wish you all well and hope that my leaving doesn't create as big a wave after you read this post <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  You never know when you may see a Blonde Dorf out of the corner of your eye <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Good hunting and best wishes... /salute<br><br>***The Dorf slings his pack on his shoulder and disappears into the setting sun***<br><br> <p><p><p align="center"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><b>MightyAxe Darkbane</b><br>  <font size="-5">59th Knight of Brell</font><font size="1"><br>  <b>Bristlebane</b></font><br>  <font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="-7">Former Leader of Forbidden Legacy<BR><img src=http://home.attbi.com/~mightyaxe/barani8.gif></td></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub52.ezboard.com/udlaren4444.showPublicProfile?language=EN>dlaren4444</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 43<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(4/14/02 10:36:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub52.ezboard.com/ffatdragonshousefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=173.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Farewell!</span><hr size=1>  /waves Goodbye to the Axeman<br> Dlaren <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=t